The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Taxi associations have threatened to strike work from Wednesday unless the waiting charge is revised. The state transport department is considering raising the waiting charge for taxis to Rs 1.25 per 2 minute 12 seconds, which was lowered from Rs 1.5 to Re 1 on Friday. Taxi operators have offered 10 per cent fare rebate to senior citizens when travelling alone or with children.     Ramakanta Das, alias Jata, 23, was arrested for attacking a woman with a stick in Mollahati in the Lake police station area on Sunday morning. Malati Naskar, 35, had objected to the use of loudspeakers during Saraswati puja by a local club, of which Das is a member. Naskar suffered head and shoulder injuries and was admitted to a nursing home.    A 150-bed diabetes clinic with ophthalmology, cardiology, dentistry, ENT, dermatology, neuromedicine, neurosurgery, oncomedicine and oncosurgery departments was inaugurated by Union minister Pranab Mukherjee on Lenin Sarani on Sunday. Sourav Ganguly and mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya were present at the inauguration.     The office of a club in Kanchrapara  Madrali United Club  was set on fire after a scuffle broke out among members on Sunday morning. Two fire tenders took an hour to douse the flames. Police said trouble started over organising a cultural event. No one was arrested in this connection.     Raja Singh, 39, was arrested late on Saturday with an illegal one-shot firearm and a live cartridge. Police said Singh was a resident of Nanda Bagan bustee, off APC Road.                                                                                                                                                                
